description:
THE END IS NIGH

The stakes are higher than ever before, as the final two Elders emerge to prevent Kyo from reaching the former Crimson King. Even more dangerous is the return of Kyoshiros burning vengeance. Terrible secrets, hidden motivations, driving desiresall are brought into the open as the ultimate climax approaches in this white-knuckle, double-stuffed volume!

Includes special extras after the story!
name: Vol. 35-36

description:
ALL PATHS LEAD HOME

The mad former Crimson King threatens to destroy all creationand only Kyoshiro stands between Demon Eyes Kyo and his ultimate foe. Beliefs are on the line as the two friends and rivals cross blades for the final time. All secrets are revealed, all scores are settled, and all life hangs in the balance. At long last, the epic conclusion of Samurai Deeper Kyo is here! Final volume.
name: Vol. 37-38

description:
Old school E.C. style horror anthology with a Heavy Metal/ Rock theme.

1,000 copies. 1st bagged CD with comic claim.

bonus 4 song E. P. by Phoenix AZ metal band "Mad Marty"

50 copies crossed signed by Jackson & Mad Marty.

Model kit release of issue #1 cover monster debuts on page 35 ad.

Notes: Cover character "Harley David" appears first in the Heavy Metal Monsters trading card set

and later on cover of "The Journal of the PBM gamer" 7th edition .

Steve Crompton of "Demi the Demoness" fame penciled and inked Dennis Worden's script for the final installment of "The Floating Skull".
name: Heavy Metal Monsters (Bonus CD)
